cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "Mergen: The execution backbone for AI coding agents"
abstract: >-
  Mergen is the execution half of the Agent Continuity Stack. It judges, with
  wisdom, how much care a task deserves (the Governor), and it proves, with
  accuracy, that the work was actually done and was no larger than it needed
  to be (the verify gate). Built entirely from public Claude Code extension
  points, with a deterministic, agent-agnostic core that runs anywhere Python
  3.9 or newer runs. Pure standard library, no network, no model.
type: software
